story. A story without stakes is an essay and is best experienced on the page,
not the stage.</li>
      <li>Start in the action. Have a great first line
that sets up the stakes or grabs attention.</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>NO: â€œSo I was thinking about climbing this mountain.
